### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe the problem.

I have a simple dto that I want to fill with extra data that isn't directly passed by the user in the POST request.

```
public class CreatePlugin
{
    [Required]
    [JsonProperty("name"), JsonPropertyName("name")]
    public string Name { get; set; }

    [Required]
    [JsonProperty("description"), JsonPropertyName("description")]
    public string Description { get; set; }

    [Required]
    [JsonProperty("version"), JsonPropertyName("version")]
    public string Version { get; set; }

    [Required]
    [JsonProperty("public"), JsonPropertyName("public")]
    public bool Public { get; set; }

    [BindProperty(BinderType = typeof(CreatedByModelBinder))]
    [ModelBinder(BinderType = typeof(CreatedByModelBinder))]
    [Newtonsoft.Json.JsonConverter(typeof(CreatedByConverter))]
    [SwaggerIgnore]
    [JsonProperty("created_by"), JsonPropertyName("created_by")]
    public int CreatedBy { get; set; }
}
```

My controller inherits `ControllerBase` and has `ApiController` attribute.
My method looks like this:

```
[HttpPost]
[Produces("application/json")]
[ProducesResponseType(typeof(Plugin), (int)HttpStatusCode.OK)]
public async Task<IActionResult> Add(CreatePlugin plugin)
{
  //some logic
  return Ok();
}
```

My custom model binder:     
```
public class CreatedByModelBinder : IModelBinder
{
    private readonly IIdentityContext _identityContext;
    public CreatedByModelBinder(IIdentityContext identityContext) => _identityContext = identityContext;

    public Task BindModelAsync(ModelBindingContext bindingContext)
    {
        var model = _identityContext.UserId;
        bindingContext.Result = ModelBindingResult.Success(model);

        return Task.CompletedTask;
    }
}

```

Problem is that ModelBinder doesn't work with `FromBody` attribute (https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/37774#issuecomment-949844941).

We should be able to use custom property binders even when we use `FromBody` attributes.

### Describe the solution you'd like

As mentioned above I'd like to be able to fill my model with additional data coming from cookie, session, query, headers, claims, and other places.

### Additional context

I've found a similar issue (https://github.com/dotnet/aspnetcore/issues/37774), @pranavkm suggested there that the author should create a custom JsonConverter.
This approach will work if you pass specific field in the json request body, but will fail if that field isn't present (in my case I want the `created_by` field to contain user id from jwt token)

`JsonConverter` approach will work if I POST this data:

```json
{
    "name": "test",
    "description": "sample description",
    "version": "1.0",
    "public": true,
    "created_by": "this will be filled"
}
```

but not his:

```json
{
    "name": "test",
    "description": "sample description",
    "version": "1.0",
    "public": true
}
```

